# Build
/build/
/dist/
*.o
*.tmp

# Resolved deps (auto-generated by cyrius deps) — NEVER commit these; CI
# regenerates the whole lib/ tree from the pinned toolchain via `cyrius deps`
# (patra's model — it tracks zero lib files). Committing them shadows the
# generated set: on a toolchain bump the stale committed libs make CI's
# `cyrius deps` fail with "cannot read ./lib/<module>.cyr" for any module the
# old set lacked. The previous `!lib/k*.cyr` exception (it only ever matched
# the generated keccak.cyr) caused exactly that asymmetry and is removed.
cyrius.lock
lib/

# Release / toolchain artifacts
cyrius-*.tar.gz
*.tar.gz
SHA256SUMS

# Example-script scratch data (regenerated by docs/examples/*.sh)
/bbs/
/keys/

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
